Text: Hey folks, I’m about to go on a tweet storm of my own…about dark money in politics. Follow if interested (or watch live here: https://t.co/E1j1sH7YBh) 👇🏽
Name: Steve Bullock

Text: Most of us would agree SCOTUS #CitizensUnited decision was damaging to our representative democracy and to the American people’s faith in our government 1/13
Name: Steve Bullock

Text: We decried the ruling. Many raised money off it it. But we didn’t actually….do anything about it. We had a chance, but everyone said “game over” and moved on. 2/13
Name: Steve Bullock

Text: Spending by dark money groups increased from $5M in 2004 to over $300M in 2012. That’s 6,000 percent, just federal races, and just what we know about. Yes, really. 3/13
Name: Steve Bullock

Text: Some said, and still say, there’s nothing we can do until we get a different Court, a different Congress, a different President. Wrong. I chose to DO something. 4/13
Name: Steve Bullock

Text: I defended Montana’s 100-year-old ban on corporate spending in elections as Attorney General, post-#CitizensUnited. When the courts struck it down, I could have joined and said “game over.” But that’s not really my style… 5/13
Name: Steve Bullock

Text: We brought Democrats and Republicans together to pass the DISCLOSE Act, one of the nation’s most progressive campaign finance laws. 90 days out from elections, even the Koch Brothers stay out of Montana. 6/13
Name: Steve Bullock

Text: But I’m not stopping there. Let’s talk about NASCAR for a minute. Tattooed across every NASCAR drivers’ jumpsuits and over their cars are the logos of the companies sponsoring the teams. 7/13
Name: Steve Bullock

Text: If elected officials are going to be like NASCAR drivers - sponsored and supported by various special interests - we ought to at least know who’s doing the sponsoring and spending. 8/13
Name: Steve Bullock

Text: This is why I’m signing an Executive Order enacting new disclosure requirements in Montana. If we know one thing about spending in elections, it’s that big companies don’t spend out of the generosity of their big corporate hearts. 9/13
Name: Steve Bullock

Text: We’re going to make sure that if someone wants to do business with the state - to profit from taxpayer dollars - you’ve got to disclose all your efforts to influence our state elections. We won’t judge — we just wan’t to know. 10/13
Name: Steve Bullock

Text: Where #CitizensUnited opened the door for a wave of dark money, Montana will again shine a light. Montana will again stand for openness and fairness in politics. Because Montanans deserve a government that works for them, and only for them. 11/13
Name: Steve Bullock

Text: Just like Montanans did back in 1912, we have to keep fighting against the outsized influence corporations and special interests have on our elections, our elected officials, and our representative democracy. I’m going to keep fighting in Montana. 12/13
Name: Steve Bullock

Text: And I hope there’s something about Montana - in our history, our mistakes, our defiance, our triumphs - that can help cure the sickness that has plagued politics in the rest of the country for too long. 13/13
Name: Steve Bullock

Text: Money in politics is the original sin of American democracy. In 1906 a Montana newspaper editor opined that “the greatest living issue that confronts us today, is whether the corporations shall control the people, or the people shall control the corporations.”
Name: Steve Bullock

Text: The origins of the corrupting role of money in politics are as old as politics itself...but our current predicament has a special, recent catalyst that we can identify with precision: the Supreme Court’s 2010 decision in Citizens United, and the aftermath.
Name: Steve Bullock

Text: Today is the 9th Anniversary of that disastrous Supreme Court decision. Since then dark money spending in our elections went from about $5 million in 2004 to over $300 million by 2012. That’s a 6,000% increase in just two presidential cycles.
Name: Steve Bullock

Text: ...one more time for those in the back: 6,000%!
Name: Steve Bullock

Text: Money in politics is fundamentally eroding American democracy and what it should (or used to) stand for – a government “of the people, by the people, and for the people.”
Name: Steve Bullock

Text: When the Citizens United ruling came down, most decried the ruling...many raised money off of it...but they didn’t actually do anything about it. Folks had a chance to act, but instead everyone basically said “game over” and moved on.
Name: Steve Bullock

Text: Not in Montana. I govern about as far as you can get from Washington D.C. and have been able to mobilize Democrats and Republicans around the idea that there’s something deeply amiss in our political system.
Name: Steve Bullock

Text: As Attorney General I personally defended our state’s own Corrupt Practices Act of 1912 after the Citizens United decision all the way to the U.S. Supreme Court.
Name: Steve Bullock

Text: As Governor I brought together Republicans and Democrats to pass one of the most progressive campaign finance disclosure laws in the country.
Name: Steve Bullock

Text: I signed a first-of-its-kind executive order requiring the recipients of major government contracts to disclose dark money spending in elections.
Name: Steve Bullock

Text: And last year I sued the IRS and U.S. Department of Treasury over their decision to abandon disclosure requirements for major donors to dark money groups. That case is pending in federal court.
Name: Steve Bullock

Text: Campaign finance is an issue that affects every American citizen, from the halls of Congress to the kitchen tables in Montana.
Name: Steve Bullock

Text: Our hopes for the many other problems this country faces - economic inequality, climate change, affordable universal healthcare - all depend on breaking the stronghold corporations and wealthy elites have on our democratic institutions.
Name: Steve Bullock

Text: Just like we have in Montana, we have to keep fighting against the outsized influence corporations and special interests have on our elections, our elected officials, and our representative democracy.
Name: Steve Bullock

Text: I’m going to keep fighting in Montana, and I hope other states will join me...because Americans deserve no less.

Text:
Citizens United created a dangerous loophole, allowing foreign governments and corporations to spend money to influence our elections. 

Today, that begins to change in Montana.

https://t.co/vhX1J08nq8
Name: Steve Bullock

Text: In 2015, Democrats and Republicans in Montana came together to pass the DISCLOSE Act - one of the most transparent campaign finance laws in the nation. #ElectionsNotAuctions
Name: Steve Bullock

Text: The Act requires that any group spending money to influence an election must disclose how they are spending money and the source of it within 90 days of Election Day. In other words, dark money groups can't hide behind their tax status any longer in Montana. #ElectionsNotAuctions
Name: Steve Bullock

Text: We've made strides in Montana towards ensuring that our elections are truly for the people, by the people. But we have one glaring omission -- we do not have an expressed ban on foreign spending in our state elections. #ElectionsNotAuctions
Name: Steve Bullock

Text: That’s why I’m proposing to expressly outlaw foreign spending in Montana elections. #ElectionsNotAuctions
Name: Steve Bullock

Text: We’ll close the Citizens United loophole by defining corporations, governments, and nationals as “foreign influenced” if their true owners can’t spend in our elections, and are using domestic shell corporations to evade the law. #ElectionsNotAuctions
Name: Steve Bullock

Text:

Text: I’m the only one in this field who’s won in a state that Trump won — and we need to win back those places we lost. It’s not going to be enough to just be against Trump, we’ve actually got to give folks a reason to vote for us.
Name: Steve Bullock

Text:
I was raised by a single mom, and we lived paycheck to paycheck. I worked my way through college and borrowed my way through law school — and I got my shot at the American Dream. 

We all deserve that shot. That's why I'm running for President.
Name: Steve Bullock

Text: I’m here live bringing reactions straight to you. Good luck everybody! #DemDebate
Name: Steve Bullock

Text: It may be easy to avoid the price tag in DC, but as a Governor, I've got to balance my budget. We've got to pay for our proposals. Period.
Name: Steve Bullock

Text: It's no wonder nothing gets done in Washington. All they do is talk (often past each other).
Name: Steve Bullock
